    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_78692497" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/78692497" />
    <a title="Gail Carriger" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2277045-gail-carriger"><img alt="Gail Carriger" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1476925453p2/2277045.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/78692497?book_show_action=true">Nov 22, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gail Carriger" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gail Carriger" href="/user/show/2277045-gail-carriger">Gail Carriger</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780441775590" href="/book/show/535392.Sorcery_Cecelia">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2277045-gail-carriger?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2277045-gail-carriger?shelf=funny">funny</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2277045-gail-carriger?shelf=ya">ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2277045-gail-carriger?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2277045-gail-carriger?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2277045-gail-carriger?shelf=research">research</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2277045-gail-carriger?shelf=historical">historical</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer78692497" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7769076399941584785">One of my all time favorite books, <i>Sorcery and Cecelia</i> started out as a letter game between two brilliant writers. The authors clearly enjoyed themselves and the resulting novel is a joy to read, both as a story and as a window into the fun experienced by to marvelous authors. <br/><br/>Set in Austen-like 1817 England, which just happens to have some very polite magic rolling around, the plot is largely driven by excellent characterization, two strong heroines, and a great deal of humor. There are several</span>
  <span id="freeText7769076399941584785" style="display:none">One of my all time favorite books, <i>Sorcery and Cecelia</i> started out as a letter game between two brilliant writers. The authors clearly enjoyed themselves and the resulting novel is a joy to read, both as a story and as a window into the fun experienced by to marvelous authors. <br /><br />Set in Austen-like 1817 England, which just happens to have some very polite magic rolling around, the plot is largely driven by excellent characterization, two strong heroines, and a great deal of humor. There are several ditty-like romances, and a tidy little ending that makes for an amuse-bouche of a read - tasty and bite sized. There are two follow up books, however, this one stands beautifully alone. Highly recommended!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7769076399941584785" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

